We are new to the neighborhood and have always had breakfast at Jimmy’s Diner on biscayne, so we figured we’d try this one out since it was closer to our house. The smell and appearance of this place is pretty dingy. The server was pretty nice and took our order. 30 mins later we began to wonder why we still hadn’t received our food since there was only 3 other tables with 2 people to each, not many people at all. We signaled to the waitress which quickly came and apologized that she accidentally put the other tables ticket twice. We received our food finally, the pancakes and waffles were extremely chewy as if the batter wasn’t mixed properly. My sons eggs looked as if they were in a pool of yolk. I had ordered hash browns on the side, which never came with the rest of the food. The waitress advised there was a mishap with the stove, that they would be out soon. Once I received the hash browns, I was almost done with the rest of my food, they were not crispy and extremely oily as if they had been sitting in oil since I ordered the breakfast. The restrooms are extremely dirty and smell horrible, to the point so gagged the breakfast I had just eaten. This place needs an upgrade in every aspect.
